				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${}^{\prime}$$\end{document} bonds. Because of low Y, NaYRuH6 and Mn-based AA′\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${}^{\prime}$$\end{document}MH6 materials can be considered stiffer materials relative to the other six semiconductors. And also, they exhibit more resistance to compression due to high K. All the μ values of the AA′\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
